Thanh Tú wrote a review May 2020
Hanoi, Vietnam15 contributions
Beautiful with good price
I stayed there for 3 nights and they had exactly what I need. Room is not so big but for a boutique hotel, it was ok. The staffs are very friendly, they only have 2 ladies work as receptionist, one in the morning and one in the afternoon. I didn't know their name so I can't mention but they do really good job. The swimming pool is next to the lobby with the massage machines which made me feel comfortable. I can take care of my daughter when she went swimming, and I can relax during that time. Not so much hotel can do that. They had ala-carte menu for breakfast change everyday, also have a small counter with some fruit juice, cakes and yogurt. A small kitchen in the room is good, but maybe should have an oven. Everyday from 6 to 8pm you can ask the receptionist for preparing…
Date of stay: May 2020
Mary Grace wrote a review Mar 2020
Koh Tao, Thailand114 contributions8 helpful votes
+1
Cozy & Serene
After the nightmare from my first hotel, I was truly hoping this place would make up for it - & it certainly has! It's so cozy, comfortable, & relaxing. All the beautiful flowers & green foliage really add to the ambience.. .Nature heals. I chose to stay here for seven nights & it was just what I needed. I loved my stay here so much that I may just come back to end my visit in Da Nang here! Jane, of the front desk, really helped my stay be as comfortable as possible. She was very intuitive in my needs, & I felt like I gained a little sister, haha. When I first arrived, there was a miscommunication through the booking site & hotel, but Jane was gracious in handling it & made sure I was happy. That's customer service! I loved all the amenities this place offered. It's the…
Date of stay: March 2020
Deeush wrote a review Mar 2020
21 contributions27 helpful votes
Lovely hotel with great service
I simply loved this place. I loved our room with cute balcony where you could just chill in the evening with glass of wine. The bed was very comfortable. Overall the room was clean (room cleaning done every day) and had a nice lemongrass smell. Breakfast was tasty, you could choose from various meals. Hotel is close to nice public beach with white sand (3min by feet) or you can use indoor pool in case of bad weather. The lady at reception was super kind and polite. Higly recommended this hotel!
Jerome C wrote a review Mar 2020
Charlotte, North Carolina5 contributions1 helpful vote
Great small hotel
The staff was super friendly. The room was large, modern and clean. The breakfast was fresh made and delicious, with lots of choices. The pool, massage chairs, sauna and free nightly foot bath was really great as well. I can't recommend this hotel enough. Great stay will be back.
Laszlo93 wrote a review Mar 2020
Rome, Italy15 contributions4 helpful votes
Quality B&B for a really good price
We had really great stay at the John Boutique Villa. I found the design really interesting, the rooms were well-equipped and the staff was really helpful. I would highlight the breakfast which was full of fresh fruits, juices and you can order different type of caffees and meals for free (and the best is that they have it until 10 AM). I definitely recommend this hotel for all type of travellers, especially for couples at all age.
Marco-Antonio wrote a review Feb 2020
London, United Kingdom306 contributions83 helpful votes
Nice hotel!
Nice hotel with friendly staff. Booked at the last minute.  The breakfast is really nice and theres a nice spread to choose from. The coffee is also delicious!  They recommended a good seafood restaurant that we ate at which was really good and a 5-10 min walk from the hotel.   The bedroom and bathroom are ok but just need a bit more sprucing up to be 5 stars.  I love their minimalist decor and calming pool area!
Date of stay: December 2019
